refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringrealpath stringpath
realpath expands all symbolic links and resolves references to '/./', '/../' and extra '/' characters in the input path and return the canonicalized absolute pathname.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     5.3.0

      Prior to this release realpath would not fail on
      *BSD systems if only the last last path
      component did not exist.

  &reftitle.examples;



    realpath example


<?php
chdir('/var/www/');
echo realpath('./../../etc/passwd');
?>


    &example.outputs;


/etc/passwd




    realpath on Windows


     On windows realpath will change unix style paths to
     windows style.



<?php
echo realpath('/windows/system32');
?>


    &example.outputs;


C:\WINDOWS\System32
